&lt;img alt=&quot;A high-tech journal device from a long lost civilization&quot; title=&quot;A high-tech journal device from a long lost civilization&quot; src=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;journal.e92e2e28b9df8437.webp&quot; srcset=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;journal.97eca71d255358a6.webp 512w, https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;journal.e92e2e28b9df8437.webp 1024w, https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.jimmyff.co.uk&#x2F;processed_images&#x2F;journal.6e4137e6844eb192.webp 2048w&quot; class=&quot;&quot; &#x2F;&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;💾 An ancient journal, left behind; hums with secrets, from a lost kind...&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&#x27;m liking the idea of a retro-futuristic vibe for the technology in my game (I was watching some Star Trek as I drew this).&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;game-play-ideas&quot;&gt;Game play ideas&lt;&#x2F;h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maybe the players are hunting these ancient high tech relics? Maybe the stargates will take the players to a high-tech world.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
</content>
        
